    "description": "Acute Coronary Syndrome (ACS) is a term used to describe a range of conditions associated with sudden reduced blood flow to the heart, which may include unstable angina and myocardial infarction (heart attack). It occurs due to the rupture of atherosclerotic plaques in the coronary arteries, leading to thrombosis and resultant ischemia of the heart muscle. ACS is a critical medical emergency that requires immediate diagnosis and treatment to restore blood flow and minimize heart damage.",
    "symptoms": [
      {
